---
title: Japanese-Style Spicy Shrimp Miso Ramen plus Bok Choy, Cabbage & Corn
description: These loaded Japanese-inspired shrimp ramen bowls are as impressive as they are satisfying, packed with tender noodles, sweet corn, a hearty mix of cabbage and bok choy, and—of course—plenty of shrimp. Sprinkle each bowl with scallions, sesame seeds, and chili flakes, then dig right in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67f38cfb23aa2ac244887e89-7dbe2fd2.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67f38cfb23aa2ac244887e89-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 1 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2670 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/japanese-style-spicy-shrimp-miso-ramen-67f38cfb23aa2ac244887e89
cuisine: East Asia
course: main course
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Drain and rinse @corn{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #medium pot{} (#large pot{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, ginger, corn, and @chili flakes{1/4%tsp} to taste (we used 1/4 tsp; 1/2 tsp for 4).

> For less heat, skip adding the chili flakes here and simply save some for serving!

Cook, stirring occasionally, until corn begins to brown slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{4%cups} to #pot{} with veggies. Stir in @miso sauce concentrate{2}, @seafood stock concentrate{1}, @ponzu sauce{18%ml}, and @rice wine vinegar{1%tbsp} (2 tbsp for 4).

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!

Bring to a boil.

Meanwhile, rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water.

Once broth is boiling, stir in shrimp and @ramen noodles{4.5%oz}. Return to a boil. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are cooked through and noodles are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once shrimp are cooked, add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%oz} to pot. Stir to combine; turn off heat.

Divide ramen between #bowls{}. Top with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Serve with any remaining chili flakes on the side for sprinkling to taste.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.